Installing Software and data for R Zoom class

1. Install R and RStudio

  • Download R @ The R Projects Home Page

    • Windows:
      • https://cran.r-project.org/bin/windows/base/R-4.0.4-win.exe
    • Mac:
      • https://cloud.r-project.org/bin/macosx/R-3.6.3.pkg
    • Linux: different distributions at link
      • https://cloud.r-project.org/bin/linux/

  • Download RStudio Desktop from RStudio

    • Windows
      • https://download1.rstudio.org/desktop/windows/RStudio-1.4.1106.exe
    • Mac
      • https://download1.rstudio.org/desktop/macos/RStudio-1.2.5033.dmg
    • Linux
      • https://www.rstudio.com/products/rstudio/download/#download

  • Run the installers for R and RStudio, in that order.

2. Open RStudio

It should look like this when you do:

3. Install additional packages and data

  • copy-paste the text below into the command window
  • hit enter
  • accept any defaults if you get prompted
  • this may take a while
install.packages(c("tidyverse", "data.table", "sf", "rmarkdown", "plotly", "hrbrthemes"))

4. Test it out

Copy-paste the following text into the command window and hit enter.

  • If the picture shows up then you should be good to go
  • Dont worry if you dont understand the commands.
library(palmerpenguins)
library(ggplot2)
library(hrbrthemes)

ggplot(data = penguins, aes(x = flipper_length_mm, y = body_mass_g, colour = species)) + 
  geom_point() + xlab("flipper length (mm)") + ylab("Body mass (g)") + 
  theme_ipsum()

5. You should be good to go
